1
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:10,133
Mrs. Althea Villaruel
Torrecampo.

2
00:00:10,267 --> 00:00:11,600
- What is this?
- I'm filing charges against you

3
00:00:11,733 --> 00:00:13,300
for what you did to my sibling.

4
00:00:13,433 --> 00:00:15,933
I am starting to make
you answer for it.

5
00:00:16,067 --> 00:00:17,733
If you do not help me,

6
00:00:17,867 --> 00:00:19,333
I will tell the truth

7
00:00:19,467 --> 00:00:21,033
that something happened
between us before.

8
00:00:21,167 --> 00:00:23,233
And Ashley is our child.

9
00:00:23,367 --> 00:00:25,367
There is no probable cause.

10
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:26,667
It is clean on paper .

11
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:29,767
Her bone marrow is no longer
recovering the way we expected.

12
00:00:29,900 --> 00:00:31,833
Oh my God. Jasmine!

13
00:00:31,967 --> 00:00:33,867
It would be faster
if the donor is a sibling .

14
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:35,967
Does Jasmine have a sibling?

15
00:00:36,133 --> 00:00:37,767
She has no sibling.

16
00:00:37,900 --> 00:00:38,867
Where are you going?

17
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:40,100
I am tired!

18
00:00:40,233 --> 00:00:42,433
You cannot take Ashley with you!

19
00:00:42,567 --> 00:00:44,167
She is not your child!

20
00:00:44,300 --> 00:00:45,300
What?

21
00:01:37,700 --> 00:01:40,500
Oh, what is this new stunt?

22
00:01:40,667 --> 00:01:41,700
And who is that?

23
00:01:45,467 --> 00:01:47,700
Mrs. Althea Villaruel
Torrecampo.

24
00:01:49,333 --> 00:01:50,900
This is a demand letter.

25
00:01:56,467 --> 00:02:06,367
[INTENSE MUSIC]

26
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:08,067
What is this?

27
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:11,333
Notice of intent to file
criminal and civil cases.

28
00:02:11,467 --> 00:02:15,033
In short, I am suing you
for what you did to my sibling.

29
00:02:15,200 --> 00:02:16,267
Unlike you,

30
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:19,967
I have the decency to inform you
before I ruin your life.

31
00:02:24,067 --> 00:02:25,467
You are just wasting your time.

32
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:26,800
You do not have proof.

33
00:02:30,633 --> 00:02:33,467
We have medical records and a
sworn statement from the victim.

34
00:02:42,267 --> 00:02:43,500
You are really doing this?

35
00:02:43,633 --> 00:02:45,100
I should have done this
a long time ago.

36
00:02:45,233 --> 00:02:47,233
Be grateful I gave you time.

37
00:02:48,433 --> 00:02:49,967
The details are written there.

38
00:02:50,100 --> 00:02:51,367
You know how to read, right?

39
00:02:51,500 --> 00:02:52,633
Read it.

40
00:02:58,033 --> 00:03:00,167
And you think
this will scare me?

41
00:03:01,067 --> 00:03:03,300
This is not a threat, Thea.

42
00:03:03,433 --> 00:03:06,100
I am starting to make you answer
for it.

43
00:03:06,233 --> 00:03:07,667
What do you want next?

44
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:09,400
I have many cases I can file

45
00:03:09,533 --> 00:03:11,467
against a homewrecker like you.

46
00:03:13,733 --> 00:03:15,100
I will see you in court.

47
00:03:19,367 --> 00:03:27,633
[INTENSE MUSIC]

48
00:03:34,567 --> 00:03:35,567
Paolo.

49
00:03:37,267 --> 00:03:39,033
What are you doing here?

50
00:03:39,167 --> 00:03:41,300
You would not answer
my calls or texts.

51
00:03:48,700 --> 00:03:51,100
Of course! I blocked you.

52
00:03:51,233 --> 00:03:53,467
And if you still have any
respect for yourself,

53
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:56,833
you would not walk into my room
after what happened.

54
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,900
Can you please leave now?

55
00:03:59,033 --> 00:04:00,200
Paolo...

56
00:04:00,333 --> 00:04:03,100
do you know Marj is suing me
over what happened to Jobert?

57
00:04:04,167 --> 00:04:05,700
Paolo, please help me.

58
00:04:05,833 --> 00:04:07,833
Convince Marj to drop the case.

59
00:04:07,967 --> 00:04:10,467
Marj and I are not okay.

60
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:13,300
If you are truly innocent,
you have nothing to fear.

61
00:04:15,900 --> 00:04:17,700
Unless...

62
00:04:17,833 --> 00:04:19,367
you really pushed Jobert down
the stairs.

63
00:04:24,033 --> 00:04:25,533
Why?

64
00:04:25,667 --> 00:04:27,767
You are accountable too!

65
00:04:27,933 --> 00:04:30,767
I did things that night because
of what happened between us.

66
00:04:30,900 --> 00:04:33,000
Which you forced!

67
00:04:33,133 --> 00:04:34,033
You know what, we are done here.

68
00:04:34,167 --> 00:04:35,367
Can you please leave now?

69
00:04:41,233 --> 00:04:43,700
Okay, fine!

70
00:04:43,833 --> 00:04:45,900
If you do not help me,

71
00:04:46,033 --> 00:04:48,233
I will tell the truth.

72
00:04:48,367 --> 00:04:50,233
That something happened
between us before.

73
00:04:50,367 --> 00:04:51,867
And Ashley...

74
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,567
is our child.

75
00:04:53,700 --> 00:04:56,033
I will tell Marj and everyone.

76
00:04:58,600 --> 00:05:01,233
Do not add more damage
to my life, Thea!

77
00:05:02,533 --> 00:05:05,100
This is the last time
you will disrupt my family.

78
00:05:05,233 --> 00:05:07,467
Hey!

79
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:10,467
If you don't want to drag others
down, then follow me.

80
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:12,267
Because if I go to jail, Paolo,

81
00:05:12,400 --> 00:05:13,433
I will bring you down with me!

82
00:05:14,833 --> 00:05:16,333
I'll make sure first,

83
00:05:16,467 --> 00:05:20,800
your dying marriage
with Marj collapses.

84
00:05:20,933 --> 00:05:30,900
[INTENSE MUSIC]

85
00:05:41,233 --> 00:05:43,167
I heard...

86
00:05:43,300 --> 00:05:46,667
you are suing Thea
over what happened to Jobert.

87
00:05:49,833 --> 00:05:51,900
The fiscal hearing
is next week,

88
00:05:52,033 --> 00:05:54,867
so maybe you can accompany
Jasmine to chemo for now.

89
00:05:57,033 --> 00:06:01,200
Sure, I will take care of her.

90
00:06:01,333 --> 00:06:03,167
But...

91
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:05,133
will you still pursue
the complaint

92
00:06:05,267 --> 00:06:08,633
even if Ashley said
there was no foul play?

93
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:17,467
Well, what matters more
right now is Jasmine.

94
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:19,600
Rather than chasing a case...

95
00:06:20,900 --> 00:06:24,700
that could further destroy
the family.

96
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:27,767
[INTENSE MUSIC]

97
00:06:27,900 --> 00:06:30,200
Paolo, this is not gossip
or a misunderstanding.

98
00:06:31,767 --> 00:06:33,600
Jobert saw your depravity.

99
00:06:35,367 --> 00:06:37,500
Your mistress attempted
something on him.

100
00:06:37,633 --> 00:06:39,367
My sibling almost died!

101
00:06:41,633 --> 00:06:43,300
I will not drop the case.

102
00:06:45,300 --> 00:06:49,433
Just to show everyone
that our family is intact?

103
00:06:49,567 --> 00:06:53,600
Or to clean your name
that already reeks of filth?

104
00:06:56,267 --> 00:06:58,700
I will not drop the case.

105
00:06:58,833 --> 00:07:01,200
I will fight this in court
even if I am alone.

106
00:07:03,633 --> 00:07:12,600
[INTENSE MUSIC]

107
00:07:15,133 --> 00:07:17,900
Go home!
I do not need you here.

108
00:07:19,133 --> 00:07:21,133
No!

109
00:07:21,267 --> 00:07:22,767
I will repeat it.

110
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:24,433
You can go back to work.

111
00:07:24,567 --> 00:07:26,333
You do not need to accompany me.

112
00:07:26,467 --> 00:07:27,800
No.

113
00:07:27,933 --> 00:07:29,533
I'll not let yoube alone here.

114
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:33,033
Whatever happened between
us,

115
00:07:33,167 --> 00:07:35,967
Jobert is my family too.

116
00:07:36,100 --> 00:07:38,600
And you should not be alone
in this fight.

117
00:07:38,733 --> 00:07:42,900
Especially since I am part
of the reason it came to this.

118
00:07:43,633 --> 00:07:46,333
Can you not turn this
into a redemption arc?

119
00:07:46,467 --> 00:07:49,100
Because you are not the one
I am suing.

120
00:07:59,733 --> 00:08:00,667
Take your seats.

121
00:08:04,633 --> 00:08:07,967
For the record, this is only
a preliminary investigation.

122
00:08:08,100 --> 00:08:11,533
We will proceed
based on affidavits.

123
00:08:11,667 --> 00:08:15,167
Verbal statements
are for clarification only.

124
00:08:15,300 --> 00:08:17,200
Mrs. Marjorie Torrecampo,

125
00:08:17,333 --> 00:08:20,900
briefly state the basis
of your complaint.

126
00:08:21,067 --> 00:08:22,700
The respondent has motive.

127
00:08:23,700 --> 00:08:28,800
My sibling caught my spouse
and the respondent in an affair.

128
00:08:29,900 --> 00:08:33,833
When the respondent confronted
my sibling near the stairs,

129
00:08:33,967 --> 00:08:36,133
my sibling fell
and went into a coma.

130
00:08:36,267 --> 00:08:37,533
I am not a murderer!

131
00:08:37,667 --> 00:08:38,833
I did not hurt him!

132
00:08:38,967 --> 00:08:41,133
- Stop it, Thea!
- I am innocent!

133
00:08:41,267 --> 00:08:43,033
You are destroying me!

134
00:08:43,167 --> 00:08:44,000
Please, sit down.

135
00:08:45,333 --> 00:08:47,867
Your denial is noted,
Mrs. Torrecampo.

136
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:51,633
This is not a venue
for confrontation.

137
00:08:51,767 --> 00:08:54,233
That woman is just taking
revenge because she blames me

138
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:57,033
for the collapse of their
marriage.

139
00:08:57,167 --> 00:09:00,800
You are even using your sibling
to destroy me?

140
00:09:00,933 --> 00:09:03,400
Marj, have pity on your sibling.

141
00:09:03,533 --> 00:09:05,767
You can no longer twist this,
Thea.

142
00:09:10,900 --> 00:09:14,933
You think your accusations
will bring me down?

143
00:09:15,067 --> 00:09:16,800
Do not target me.

144
00:09:16,933 --> 00:09:18,967
The one you should be suing
is beside you.

145
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:21,200
I owe you nothing, Marj.

146
00:09:21,333 --> 00:09:23,433
I never promised
to be faithful to you.

147
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:26,500
Do not tell me who to sue,

148
00:09:26,633 --> 00:09:29,033
because this is not about my
spouse.

149
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:31,933
This is about someone weaker
than you,

150
00:09:32,067 --> 00:09:36,300
whom you chose to push down the
stairs to cover up your crime.

151
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:41,833
[INTENSE MUSIC]

152
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:46,267
If either of you cannot conduct
yourselves accordingly,

153
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:48,233
I will terminate
this proceeding.

154
00:09:48,367 --> 00:09:51,500
You will all await
this office's resolution.

155
00:09:51,633 --> 00:09:52,633
That is all.

156
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:59,333
[INTENSE MUSIC]

157
00:10:06,433 --> 00:10:08,167
Thank you for being...

158
00:10:08,300 --> 00:10:09,567
here with me, Xander.

159
00:10:13,267 --> 00:10:18,533
I do not really have anyone else
to talk to right now.

160
00:10:18,667 --> 00:10:20,300
I feel so ashamed
in front of Jasmine.

161
00:10:21,567 --> 00:10:26,167
Especially now that our moms
are also in a legal battle.

162
00:10:26,300 --> 00:10:27,733
I do not know.

163
00:10:27,867 --> 00:10:29,900
No matter how hard we try
to stay strong,

164
00:10:30,033 --> 00:10:32,667
our parents still find ways
to drive us apart.

165
00:10:35,033 --> 00:10:36,867
You and Jasmine,
it is not your fault.

166
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:39,933
But we are the ones suffering.

167
00:10:41,767 --> 00:10:43,367
I am so sorry
you are seeing me like this.

168
00:10:46,300 --> 00:10:48,033
You do not need to say sorry.

169
00:10:48,167 --> 00:10:50,700
I know you are stressed out.

170
00:10:50,833 --> 00:10:55,233
But, Ash,
you impress me even more.

171
00:10:55,367 --> 00:10:57,300
Even with all the...

172
00:10:57,433 --> 00:10:59,533
chaos...

173
00:10:59,667 --> 00:11:02,033
and issues in your family,

174
00:11:02,167 --> 00:11:03,967
you are still the glue
holding everyone together.

175
00:11:06,300 --> 00:11:08,067
That is not weakness.

176
00:11:08,233 --> 00:11:10,167
That is real strength, Ashley.

177
00:11:10,300 --> 00:11:20,267
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

178
00:12:05,567 --> 00:12:09,533
You might be the bravest girl
I have ever known.

179
00:12:09,667 --> 00:12:13,567
So, you do not need to say
sorry.

180
00:12:13,700 --> 00:12:15,167
If anything,

181
00:12:15,333 --> 00:12:16,600
I admire you even more, Ash.

182
00:12:19,533 --> 00:12:25,233
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

183
00:12:25,367 --> 00:12:27,000
After evaluation

184
00:12:27,133 --> 00:12:30,867
of the affidavits and records
submitted,

185
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:36,667
this office finds no probable
cause to indict the respondent.

186
00:12:39,667 --> 00:12:41,733
Attorney, what does this mean?

187
00:12:41,867 --> 00:12:44,267
They said our evidence is weak.

188
00:12:44,400 --> 00:12:46,333
What?

189
00:12:46,467 --> 00:12:48,333
The sustained injuries,

190
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:49,633
while serious,

191
00:12:49,767 --> 00:12:53,267
are not sufficient to establish
criminal liability...

192
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:56,467
beyond speculation.

193
00:12:56,600 --> 00:13:00,933
Accordingly, the complaint
is hereby dismissed.

194
00:13:01,067 --> 00:13:02,367
What?

195
00:13:02,500 --> 00:13:04,133
This cannot be right!

196
00:13:04,267 --> 00:13:07,033
My sibling went into a coma
after being allowed to fall,

197
00:13:07,167 --> 00:13:10,633
and you are telling me
this case has no basis?

198
00:13:10,767 --> 00:13:12,500
What kind of law is this?

199
00:13:12,633 --> 00:13:14,733
What, do we have to wait
for my sibling to die

200
00:13:14,867 --> 00:13:16,700
before you listen to us?

201
00:13:16,833 --> 00:13:18,333
This is not right.

202
00:13:18,467 --> 00:13:20,233
I cannot understand this!

203
00:13:24,067 --> 00:13:25,100
[MUMBLING]

204
00:13:25,233 --> 00:13:27,533
No, wait! This cannot be!

205
00:13:27,667 --> 00:13:37,633
[INTENSE MUSIC]

206
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:39,133
Is that it?

207
00:13:39,267 --> 00:13:40,667
As if nothing happened?

208
00:13:40,800 --> 00:13:43,600
Jobert almost died, Mom.

209
00:13:43,733 --> 00:13:46,600
[Speaking in Visayan language]

210
00:13:51,300 --> 00:13:53,700
The truth will come out,
my child.

211
00:13:57,367 --> 00:14:00,567
I do not know
how I can let this go.

212
00:14:02,133 --> 00:14:05,167
I cannot just let this
go so easily, Mom.

213
00:14:05,300 --> 00:14:09,867
Marj, you do not have
to let it go.

214
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:12,367
Just set it aside for now,
my child.

215
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:16,467
Focus first
on your child's healing

216
00:14:16,600 --> 00:14:18,267
and your sibling's recovery.

217
00:14:19,433 --> 00:14:21,567
After that,

218
00:14:21,700 --> 00:14:23,233
when things are better,

219
00:14:23,367 --> 00:14:26,667
you can come back to it.

220
00:14:26,800 --> 00:14:30,600
Marj, this is more important
than your fight with Thea.

221
00:14:30,767 --> 00:14:40,733
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

222
00:14:48,333 --> 00:14:58,300
[INTENSE MUSIC]

223
00:15:15,533 --> 00:15:17,567
No probable cause.

224
00:15:17,700 --> 00:15:19,467
No corroboration.

225
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:21,133
Clean on paper.

226
00:15:22,300 --> 00:15:23,967
And this never happened.

227
00:15:26,133 --> 00:15:26,900
Thank you!

228
00:15:27,033 --> 00:15:28,233
Thank you!

229
00:15:28,367 --> 00:15:37,233
[INTENSE MUSIC]

230
00:15:40,967 --> 00:15:47,733
[PHONE KEYS CLICKING]

231
00:15:47,867 --> 00:15:51,567
[INTENSE MUSIC]

232
00:15:51,700 --> 00:15:54,300
[LINE RINGING]

233
00:15:54,433 --> 00:15:56,267
It is done!

234
00:15:56,400 --> 00:15:58,500
Okay, good!

235
00:15:58,633 --> 00:16:01,867
Just make sure you keep
your end of the bargain.

236
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:05,033
A deal is a deal, Paolo.

237
00:16:06,833 --> 00:16:09,533
So, do you not want
to celebrate...

238
00:16:09,700 --> 00:16:12,267
[CALL DISCONNECTED]

239
00:16:12,400 --> 00:16:13,333
Hello?

240
00:16:14,733 --> 00:16:16,833
Hello?

241
00:16:16,967 --> 00:16:21,033
[INTENSE MUSIC]

242
00:16:21,167 --> 00:16:29,600
[PHONE RINGING]

243
00:16:29,733 --> 00:16:31,967
[SOBBING]

244
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:36,467
[SOBBING]

245
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:44,600
Jas? What happened?

246
00:16:44,767 --> 00:16:46,067
Why are you crying?

247
00:16:47,933 --> 00:16:49,133
It is nothing, Mom.

248
00:16:49,267 --> 00:16:50,933
I was just in the bathroom.

249
00:16:53,567 --> 00:16:56,100
[INTENSE MUSIC]

250
00:16:56,233 --> 00:16:57,833
Jasmine.

251
00:16:57,967 --> 00:16:59,500
Oh my God.

252
00:16:59,633 --> 00:17:01,167
Jasmine!

253
00:17:01,300 --> 00:17:02,600
Paolo!

254
00:17:02,733 --> 00:17:03,667
Paolo!

255
00:17:03,800 --> 00:17:05,333
My child!

256
00:17:05,467 --> 00:17:06,233
Wake up!

257
00:17:06,367 --> 00:17:08,267
Paolo, help!

258
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:12,900
Her bone marrow is no longer
recovering the way we expected.

259
00:17:13,033 --> 00:17:14,500
If we want to be proactive,

260
00:17:14,633 --> 00:17:17,700
we need to start considering
a stem cell transplant.

261
00:17:17,867 --> 00:17:19,200
All right, Doctor.

262
00:17:19,333 --> 00:17:22,933
Whatever we need to do
to help Jasmine.

263
00:17:23,067 --> 00:17:25,633
I will look into it and prepare
the options and procedures

264
00:17:25,767 --> 00:17:28,367
so you will be well informed.
Excuse me, Ma'am.

265
00:17:39,333 --> 00:17:42,167
I thought she was responding
well to the chemo.

266
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:47,200
Her body cannot handle
the chemo after all.

267
00:17:48,567 --> 00:17:51,000
Or is it us
that she cannot handle?

268
00:17:55,600 --> 00:17:56,767
No, Marj.

269
00:17:56,900 --> 00:18:00,967
The doctor said
there is still an option.

270
00:18:01,100 --> 00:18:02,767
The stem cell treatment.

271
00:18:03,833 --> 00:18:06,200
Marj, it is like this...

272
00:18:06,333 --> 00:18:12,167
Chemo is like trying to fix
a house during a storm.

273
00:18:12,300 --> 00:18:17,567
Stem cells are like resetting
the foundation.

274
00:18:17,700 --> 00:18:19,667
Everything damaged is removed

275
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:22,567
so something stronger
can be rebuilt.

276
00:18:22,733 --> 00:18:24,800
That means...

277
00:18:24,933 --> 00:18:26,500
this is a different battle.

278
00:18:26,633 --> 00:18:36,600
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

279
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:38,900
I am so tired, Paolo.

280
00:18:40,333 --> 00:18:41,533
Jasmine too.

281
00:18:43,167 --> 00:18:44,333
Me too.

282
00:18:45,567 --> 00:18:47,033
But she is not done yet.

283
00:18:49,133 --> 00:18:50,700
Neither are we.

284
00:18:50,833 --> 00:19:00,800
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

285
00:19:10,867 --> 00:19:11,967
Ash.

286
00:19:18,900 --> 00:19:20,600
Talk to me.

287
00:19:21,633 --> 00:19:22,800
What is happening?

288
00:19:27,467 --> 00:19:28,733
It is Jasmine.

289
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:32,467
She is ghosting me.

290
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:35,133
I think she is angry at me.

291
00:19:40,733 --> 00:19:42,467
And why would that be?

292
00:19:46,200 --> 00:19:48,200
Maybe because of Mom.

293
00:19:50,567 --> 00:19:53,933
She probably feels
like I chose Mom.

294
00:19:54,067 --> 00:19:57,367
I had no choice, Dad.

295
00:19:57,500 --> 00:19:59,900
I just wanted to help.

296
00:20:00,033 --> 00:20:02,600
I just wanted to protect Mom.

297
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:08,467
But because of what I did,

298
00:20:11,367 --> 00:20:13,467
I feel even more guilty.

299
00:20:14,667 --> 00:20:16,067
Guilty?

300
00:20:17,367 --> 00:20:19,367
Why would you feel guilty

301
00:20:19,500 --> 00:20:21,167
if you are just helping
your mom?

302
00:20:23,167 --> 00:20:24,067
Dad.

303
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:25,767
My child.

304
00:20:25,900 --> 00:20:27,033
Why do you feel guilty?

305
00:20:27,167 --> 00:20:30,167
[INTENSE MUSIC]

306
00:20:30,400 --> 00:20:31,200
I lied.

307
00:20:32,267 --> 00:20:33,967
About what?

308
00:20:39,667 --> 00:20:41,700
About Uncle Jobert.

309
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:46,500
It is not true
that I saw him fall.

310
00:20:48,500 --> 00:20:49,600
When I arrived there,

311
00:20:49,733 --> 00:20:51,667
he was already
at the bottom of the stairs.

312
00:20:54,233 --> 00:20:56,233
Mom forced me.

313
00:20:58,900 --> 00:21:02,167
She told me that if I did
not cover for her,

314
00:21:04,300 --> 00:21:06,567
our family would be destroyed.

315
00:21:06,700 --> 00:21:14,133
[INTENSE MUSIC]

316
00:21:14,300 --> 00:21:16,000
She should not have done that.

317
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:19,700
You should not have
been dragged into this.

318
00:21:23,433 --> 00:21:33,400
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

319
00:21:45,767 --> 00:21:49,433
Thank you for your time today,
Mr. and Mrs. Torrecampo.

320
00:21:49,567 --> 00:21:52,133
Our next step
is to look for a donor

321
00:21:52,267 --> 00:21:55,100
whose tissue marker
matches Jasmine's.

322
00:21:55,233 --> 00:21:57,267
We usually start
with the immediate family.

323
00:21:58,633 --> 00:22:00,233
Yes, we will have ourselves
tested immediately.

324
00:22:00,367 --> 00:22:02,600
Yes, that is standard.

325
00:22:02,733 --> 00:22:05,500
I am sure
that at least one of you

326
00:22:05,633 --> 00:22:08,833
could be a possible bridge
or temporary donor.

327
00:22:12,167 --> 00:22:15,433
Well, actually, it is faster if
the donor is a sibling.

328
00:22:16,767 --> 00:22:19,267
There is less risk of rejection.

329
00:22:19,400 --> 00:22:22,067
Does Jasmine have a sibling?

330
00:22:22,200 --> 00:22:25,133
Jasmine is our only child.

331
00:22:26,533 --> 00:22:27,800
She has no sibling.

332
00:22:27,933 --> 00:22:37,900
[INTENSE MUSIC]

333
00:22:39,767 --> 00:22:42,267
Ashley!

334
00:22:42,400 --> 00:22:44,867
Look what I bought for you.

335
00:22:48,700 --> 00:22:50,000
Where are you going?

336
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:53,767
Wait, these are Ashley's things.

337
00:22:55,700 --> 00:22:57,533
I dropped Ashley off
at the café.

338
00:22:57,667 --> 00:23:00,100
- What?
- I will pick her up from there.

339
00:23:00,233 --> 00:23:01,633
You can stay here if you want.

340
00:23:01,767 --> 00:23:03,433
But I have had enough.

341
00:23:03,567 --> 00:23:05,333
What is this now?

342
00:23:05,467 --> 00:23:07,433
You are leaving me?

343
00:23:07,567 --> 00:23:10,533
Enough of you
deceiving and using me.

344
00:23:10,667 --> 00:23:14,167
But using my child,
teaching her to lie,

345
00:23:14,300 --> 00:23:16,800
to cover for you,
and protect yourself?

346
00:23:18,233 --> 00:23:21,200
Edward, no!
You misunderstood that.

347
00:23:21,333 --> 00:23:23,500
Edward, I did that for us.

348
00:23:23,667 --> 00:23:25,333
You know,

349
00:23:25,467 --> 00:23:27,767
I regret marrying you.

350
00:23:31,033 --> 00:23:34,300
Ashley is the best thing
that ever happened in my life.

351
00:23:35,567 --> 00:23:37,300
And I will take her away
from you

352
00:23:37,433 --> 00:23:39,967
before you destroy her
completely.

353
00:23:40,100 --> 00:23:41,900
Take that back!

354
00:23:42,033 --> 00:23:43,433
No!

355
00:23:43,567 --> 00:23:46,367
You are the most vile person
I know.

356
00:23:48,167 --> 00:23:51,067
And I will not let my child
turn out like you.

357
00:23:52,033 --> 00:23:53,500
Edward, please!

358
00:23:53,633 --> 00:23:55,000
Edward, please, do not leave me!

359
00:23:55,167 --> 00:23:57,267
I am done! Enough!

360
00:23:58,767 --> 00:24:00,000
I am exhausted.

361
00:24:00,133 --> 00:24:01,733
Do whatever you want
with your life!

362
00:24:03,933 --> 00:24:05,733
We are leaving you!

363
00:24:05,867 --> 00:24:08,667
I am done with you
and this family!

364
00:24:08,800 --> 00:24:09,967
No!

365
00:24:10,100 --> 00:24:11,700
Me and my child!

366
00:24:11,833 --> 00:24:21,267
[INTENSE MUSIC]

367
00:24:21,600 --> 00:24:23,167
Edward, please.
Let us talk about this.

368
00:24:24,200 --> 00:24:26,833
Ashley cannot be taken
away from me, please.

369
00:24:26,967 --> 00:24:28,533
What?

370
00:24:28,700 --> 00:24:29,967
For what?

371
00:24:30,833 --> 00:24:34,167
So you can have a free pass,
a ticket to stay in this house?

372
00:24:35,733 --> 00:24:39,000
So you can have an alibi for all
the wrong things you have done?

373
00:24:40,233 --> 00:24:41,800
This ends now, Thea!

374
00:24:41,933 --> 00:24:43,167
No!

375
00:24:43,300 --> 00:24:45,367
I am sorry!

376
00:24:45,500 --> 00:24:47,600
I just made a mistake!
I was just scared, Edward.

377
00:24:47,733 --> 00:24:48,767
Scared?

378
00:24:50,033 --> 00:24:52,833
Yet you had no shame
using our child?

379
00:24:53,933 --> 00:24:55,233
Enough!

380
00:24:55,367 --> 00:24:56,867
Thea,
you will not fool me anymore!

381
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:59,233
You will not deceive me again!

382
00:24:59,367 --> 00:25:02,200
You cannot take Ashley with you!
She is my child!

383
00:25:02,367 --> 00:25:04,033
And she is my child too!

384
00:25:05,167 --> 00:25:06,733
Between the two of us,

385
00:25:06,867 --> 00:25:09,400
I know better
what is good for her.

386
00:25:09,533 --> 00:25:10,733
No!

387
00:25:10,867 --> 00:25:12,500
You do not!

388
00:25:12,633 --> 00:25:15,233
Because you have no right
to her!

389
00:25:15,367 --> 00:25:17,767
She is not your child!

390
00:25:17,900 --> 00:25:19,300
What?

391
00:25:19,433 --> 00:25:20,833
Ashley cannot be taken away
from me!

392
00:25:20,967 --> 00:25:23,033
You cannot take her from me!

393
00:25:23,167 --> 00:25:25,000
You are not her father!

394
00:25:26,433 --> 00:25:28,933
She is Paolo's child!

395
00:25:29,067 --> 00:25:31,667
[INTENSE MUSIC]

396
00:25:31,800 --> 00:25:32,867
[SLAPS]

397
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:38,967
[INTENSE MUSIC]

398
00:25:39,133 --> 00:25:40,233
[SLAPS]

399
00:25:40,367 --> 00:25:50,333
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

400
00:25:55,733 --> 00:25:58,300
From the very beginning,
you have been deceiving me!

401
00:25:58,433 --> 00:26:00,967
Everything you did,
everything you said,

402
00:26:01,100 --> 00:26:04,633
everything you showed me,
all of it was a lie!

403
00:26:04,767 --> 00:26:06,733
Why did you have to lie to me?

404
00:26:06,867 --> 00:26:10,333
Because that was the deal
between your father and Paolo.

405
00:26:10,500 --> 00:26:12,667
You knew,
but you did not tell me?

406
00:26:12,800 --> 00:26:14,000
I do not know
what you are talking about!

407
00:26:14,133 --> 00:26:15,733
Edward already knows
about Ashley.

408
00:26:15,867 --> 00:26:16,867
I had to tell him the truth,

409
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:18,567
or he would take her away
from me.

410
00:26:18,700 --> 00:26:19,900
What are we going to do?

411
00:26:20,933 --> 00:26:23,800
[Speaking in Visayan language]

412
00:26:23,933 --> 00:26:25,267
He seems worried.

413
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:28,800
He told me he is afraid
of suddenly losing the client.

414
00:26:28,933 --> 00:26:29,967
I needed you, Dad!

415
00:26:30,100 --> 00:26:32,700
I needed a father
who would protect me.

416
00:26:32,833 --> 00:26:36,067
But instead, you kept
your golden child shiny,

417
00:26:36,200 --> 00:26:38,967
beautiful,
and perfect in front of others,

418
00:26:39,100 --> 00:26:40,700
at my expense!

419
00:26:40,833 --> 00:26:44,133
You know what, you are
a completely worthless father!

420
00:26:47,867 --> 00:26:49,767
Ashley was the only one
on my side,

421
00:26:49,900 --> 00:26:54,067
and now I find out she was never
even mine in the first place.
